# E2E: Test fix checklist

Before marking any test fix as done, verify all items below.

---

## BYOIDC compatibility (highest priority)

- [ ] Fix works on **both** BYOIDC and non-BYOIDC clusters (see rule `05-e2e-validation-workflow.mdc`)
- [ ] BYOIDC detection uses only `is_byoidc_cluster_detected()` from `support.py` ‚Äî no new copies
- [ ] No env-var-based BYOIDC detection added (`BYOIDC_ADMIN_USERNAME`, username prefix checks, etc.)
- [ ] No `status.oidcClients` check added ‚Äî it is present on standard OpenShift 4.14+ clusters and causes false positives
- [ ] `spec.oidcProviders[].issuer.issuerURL` (not `.url`) used wherever the issuer URL is read
- [ ] Job submission is not skipped for BYOIDC ‚Äî use `get_oidc_tokens()` with `OCP_ADMIN_USER_USERNAME/PASSWORD`

## Code structure

- [ ] No `_is_byoidc_cluster()` instance method added to a test class ‚Äî call `is_byoidc_cluster_detected()` directly
- [ ] Helper functions (`get_oidc_tokens`, `get_byoidc_issuer_url`, `run_oc_command`, etc.) used from `support.py`, not re-implemented
- [ ] `import os` present in any file that uses `os.environ.get(...)` (support.py re-exports it via `*` but upgrade test must import it explicitly)

## Python 3.12 compatibility

- [ ] `pkg_resources` not used ‚Äî use `importlib.metadata` or avoid entirely. If a Ray `runtime_env` pip requirement pulls in an old library that uses `pkg_resources`, pin it to a version that does not (e.g. `pytorch_lightning>=2.0,<3.0`)
- [ ] `pytorch_lightning` imports use 2.x paths:
  ```python
  # ‚úÖ 2.x
  from pytorch_lightning.callbacks import TQDMProgressBar
  # ‚ùå 1.x
  from pytorch_lightning.callbacks.progress import TQDMProgressBar
  ```
- [ ] `Trainer` uses `use_distributed_sampler=` (not the removed `replace_sampler_ddp=`)
- [ ] `ACCELERATOR` env var defaults to `"auto"`, not `None`; map `"gpu"` ‚Üí `"cuda"` before passing to `Trainer`

## Ray runtime_env pip requirements (`mnist_pip_requirements.txt`)

- [ ] No `setuptools` added as a workaround ‚Äî upgrade the offending library instead
- [ ] `pytorch_lightning` pinned to `>=2.0,<3.0` (or exact compatible version)

## Pre-commit (must pass before finishing)

- [ ] Run `pre-commit run --all-files` and fix any failures before considering the change done
- [ ] Do not skip or alter pre-commit hooks

## Docker / image build

- [ ] After editing any file under `tests/`, rebuild the image with `--no-cache` or use `make build-test-image` (which does not cache by default via `podman build`)
- [ ] Run with `--pull="never"` to guarantee the locally built image is used

